From: Keel <ci@keel.invalid>
Subject: [PATCH 0005/0006] keel: ui: per-tab accent color tinting

Adds the per-tab tinting system described in docs/design/navbar-ideas.md:

  - KeelTabAccent: a profile-keyed service that holds, for each WebContents,
    the calmed accent color to use for that tab. Extraction order:
      1. <meta name="theme-color"> from the page <head>
      2. Dominant color of the favicon (LRU-cached per origin)
      3. Static Keel accent #53DAC6 fallback
    Saturation is clamped to HSL S ≤ 0.55, L ∈ [0.40, 0.70] so loud
    page accents stay calm in chrome.

  - Tab::OnPaint paints a 2-px left edge marker with the per-tab accent.

  - LocationBarView::OnPaint paints a 1-px bottom underline with the
    active tab's accent at 60% opacity.

  - KeelMinimalToolbar::SetActiveAccent feeds the strip glow.

The accent extractor uses Blink's existing DocumentMetadataExtractor for
the meta tag (already exposed via Mojo for things like 'add to home
screen'). The favicon dominant-color code re-uses ImageFetcher's
existing PaletteExtractor without modification.

Touches: //brave/browser/ui/* and the WebContents observer surface only.
No third_party/, no V8, no network/, no media/, no parsers.

